   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Doorstep School - School on Wheels</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The School on Wheels project introduces education to the lives of approximately 125 children for the first time and seeks to enrol them into mainstream education and keep them there with follow up programmes.   For 120/child/annum, the project provides literacy lessons, regular health checks at local hospitals, parent awareness meetings, preparation for children to enter local schools or special schools, after-school study classes and pastoral support to keep them in school.</narrative>
  </description>
